321 // Multiple clients for the same Service Bus entity should be using the same management client.
322 function getManagementClient(
323 clients: Dictionary<ClientEntityContext>,
324 entityPath: string
325 ): ManagementClient | undefined {
326 let result: ManagementClient | undefined;
327 for (const id of Object.keys(clients)) {
328 if (clients[id].entityPath === entityPath) {
329 result = clients[id].managementClient;
330 break;
331 }
332 }
333 return result;

152 /**
153 * Ensures that the token is renewed within the predefined renewal margin.
154 * @protected
155 * @returns {void}
156 */
157 protected async _ensureTokenRenewal(): Promise<void> {
158 const tokenValidTimeInSeconds = this._context.namespace.tokenProvider.tokenValidTimeInSeconds;
159 const tokenRenewalMarginInSeconds = this._context.namespace.tokenProvider
160 .tokenRenewalMarginInSeconds;
161 const nextRenewalTimeout = (tokenValidTimeInSeconds - tokenRenewalMarginInSeconds) * 1000;
162 this._tokenRenewalTimer = setTimeout(async () => {
163 try {
164 await this._negotiateClaim(true);
165 } catch (err) {

170 this._type,
171 this.name,
172 this.address,
173 err
174 );
175 }
176 }, nextRenewalTimeout);

178 "[%s] %s '%s' with address %s, has next token renewal in %d seconds @(%s).",
179 this._context.namespace.connectionId,
180 this._type,
181 this.name,
182 this.address,
183 nextRenewalTimeout / 1000,
184 new Date(Date.now() + nextRenewalTimeout).toString()
185 );
186 }

586 this._context.namespace.connectionId,
587 request.body
588 );
589 log.mgmt(
590 "[%s] Acquiring lock to get the management req res link.",
591 this._context.namespace.connectionId
592 );
593 await defaultLock.acquire(this.managementLock, () => {
594 return this._init();
595 });
596 const result = await this._mgmtReqResLink!.sendRequest(request);
597 const sequenceNumbers = result.body[Constants.sequenceNumbers];
598 const sequenceNumbersAsLong = [];
599 for (let i = 0; i < sequenceNumbers.length; i++) {
600 if (typeof sequenceNumbers[i] === "number") {
601 sequenceNumbersAsLong.push(Long.fromNumber(sequenceNumbers[i]));
602 } else {
603 sequenceNumbersAsLong.push(Long.fromBytesBE(sequenceNumbers[i]));
604 }
605 }
606 return sequenceNumbersAsLong;
607 } catch (err) {
608 const error = translate(err);
609 log.error(
610 "An error occurred while sending the request to schedule messages to " +
611 "$management endpoint: %O",
612 error
613 );
614 throw error;
615 }
616 }

618 /**
619 * Cancels an array of messages that were scheduled.
620 * @param sequenceNumbers - An Array of sequence numbers of the message to be cancelled.
621 * @returns Promise<void>
622 */
623 async cancelScheduledMessages(
624 sequenceNumbers: Long[],
625 associatedLinkName?: string
626 ): Promise<void> {
627 throwErrorIfConnectionClosed(this._context.namespace);
628 const messageBody: any = {};
629 messageBody[Constants.sequenceNumbers] = [];
630 for (let i = 0; i < sequenceNumbers.length; i++) {
631 const sequenceNumber = sequenceNumbers[i];
632 try {
633 messageBody[Constants.sequenceNumbers].push(Buffer.from(sequenceNumber.toBytesBE()));
634 } catch (err) {
635 const error = translate(err);
636 log.error(
637 "An error occurred while encoding the item at position %d in the " +
638 "sequenceNumbers array: %O",
639 i,
640 error
641 );
642 throw error;
643 }
644 }
645
646 try {
647 messageBody[Constants.sequenceNumbers] = types.wrap_array(
648 messageBody[Constants.sequenceNumbers],
649 0x81,
650 undefined
651 );
652 const request: AmqpMessage = {
653 body: messageBody,
654 message_id: generate_uuid(),
655 reply_to: this.replyTo,
656 application_properties: {
657 operation: Constants.operations.cancelScheduledMessage
658 }
659 };
660 if (associatedLinkName) {
661 request.application_properties![Constants.associatedLinkName] = associatedLinkName;
662 }
663 request.application_properties![Constants.trackingId] = generate_uuid();
664 log.mgmt(
665 "[%s] Cancel scheduled messages request body: %O.",
666 this._context.namespace.connectionId,
667 request.body
668 );
669 log.mgmt(
670 "[%s] Acquiring lock to get the management req res link.",
671 this._context.namespace.connectionId
672 );
673 await defaultLock.acquire(this.managementLock, () => {
674 return this._init();
675 });
676 await this._mgmtReqResLink!.sendRequest(request);
677 } catch (err) {
678 const error = translate(err);
679 log.error(
680 "An error occurred while sending the request to cancel the scheduled message to " +
681 "$management endpoint: %O",
682 error
683 );
684 throw error;
685 }

688 /**
689 * Receives a list of deferred messages identified by `sequenceNumbers`.
690 * @param sequenceNumbers A list containing the sequence numbers to receive.
691 * @param receiveMode The mode in which the receiver was created.
692 * @returns Promise<ServiceBusMessage[]>
693 * - Returns a list of messages identified by the given sequenceNumbers.
694 * - Returns an empty list if no messages are found.
695 * - Throws an error if the messages have not been deferred.
696 */
697 async receiveDeferredMessages(
698 sequenceNumbers: Long[],
699 receiveMode: ReceiveMode,
700 associatedLinkName?: string,
701 sessionId?: string
702 ): Promise<ServiceBusMessage[]> {
703 throwErrorIfConnectionClosed(this._context.namespace);
704
705 const messageList: ServiceBusMessage[] = [];
706 const messageBody: any = {};
707 messageBody[Constants.sequenceNumbers] = [];
708 for (let i = 0; i < sequenceNumbers.length; i++) {
709 const sequenceNumber = sequenceNumbers[i];
710 try {
711 messageBody[Constants.sequenceNumbers].push(Buffer.from(sequenceNumber.toBytesBE()));
712 } catch (err) {
713 const error = translate(err);
714 log.error(
715 "An error occurred while encoding the item at position %d in the " +
716 "sequenceNumbers array: %O",
717 i,
718 error
719 );
720 throw error;
721 }
722 }
723
724 try {
725 messageBody[Constants.sequenceNumbers] = types.wrap_array(
726 messageBody[Constants.sequenceNumbers],
727 0x81,
728 undefined
729 );
730 const receiverSettleMode: number = receiveMode === ReceiveMode.receiveAndDelete ? 0 : 1;
731 messageBody[Constants.receiverSettleMode] = types.wrap_uint(receiverSettleMode);
732 if (sessionId != null) {
733 messageBody[Constants.sessionIdMapKey] = sessionId;
734 }
735 const request: AmqpMessage = {
736 body: messageBody,
737 message_id: generate_uuid(),
738 reply_to: this.replyTo,
739 application_properties: {
740 operation: Constants.operations.receiveBySequenceNumber
741 }
742 };
743 if (associatedLinkName) {
744 request.application_properties![Constants.associatedLinkName] = associatedLinkName;
745 }
746 request.application_properties![Constants.trackingId] = generate_uuid();
747 log.mgmt(
748 "[%s] Receive deferred messages request body: %O.",
749 this._context.namespace.connectionId,
750 request.body
751 );
752 log.mgmt(
753 "[%s] Acquiring lock to get the management req res link.",
754 this._context.namespace.connectionId
755 );
756 await defaultLock.acquire(this.managementLock, () => {
757 return this._init();
758 });
759
760 const result = await this._mgmtReqResLink!.sendRequest(request);
761 const messages = result.body.messages as {
762 message: Buffer;
763 "lock-token": Buffer;
764 }[];
765 for (const msg of messages) {
766 const decodedMessage = RheaMessageUtil.decode(msg.message);
767 const message = new ServiceBusMessage(
768 this._context,
769 decodedMessage as any,
770 { tag: msg["lock-token"] } as any,
771 false
772 );
773 if (message.lockToken && message.lockedUntilUtc) {
774 this._context.requestResponseLockedMessages.set(
775 message.lockToken,
776 message.lockedUntilUtc
777 );
778 }
779 messageList.push(message);
780 }
781 return messageList;
782 } catch (err) {
783 const error = translate(err);
784 log.error(
785 "An error occurred while sending the request to receive deferred messages to " +
786 "$management endpoint: %O",
787 error
788 );
789 throw error;
790 }
791 }

865 /**
866 * Renews the lock for the specified session.
867 * @param sessionId Id of the session for which the lock needs to be renewed
868 * @param {string} associatedLinkName associated link name on which operation is to be executed, if applicable
869 * @param options Options that can be set while sending the request.
870 * @returns Promise<Date> New lock token expiry date and time in UTC format.
871 */
872 async renewSessionLock(
873 sessionId: string,
874 associatedLinkName?: string,
875 options?: SendRequestOptions
876 ): Promise<Date> {
877 throwErrorIfConnectionClosed(this._context.namespace);
878 if (!options) options = {};
879 if (options.delayInSeconds == null) options.delayInSeconds = 1;
880 if (options.timeoutInSeconds == null) options.timeoutInSeconds = 5;
881 if (options.times == null) options.times = 5;
882 try {
883 const messageBody: any = {};
884 messageBody[Constants.sessionIdMapKey] = sessionId;
885 const request: AmqpMessage = {
886 body: messageBody,
887 reply_to: this.replyTo,
888 application_properties: {
889 operation: Constants.operations.renewSessionLock
890 }
891 };
892 request.application_properties![Constants.trackingId] = generate_uuid();
893 if (associatedLinkName) {
894 request.application_properties![Constants.associatedLinkName] = associatedLinkName;
895 }
896 log.mgmt(
897 "[%s] Renew Session Lock request body: %O.",
898 this._context.namespace.connectionId,
899 request.body
900 );
901 log.mgmt(
902 "[%s] Acquiring lock to get the management req res link.",
903 this._context.namespace.connectionId
904 );
905 await defaultLock.acquire(this.managementLock, () => {
906 return this._init();
907 });
908 const result = await this._mgmtReqResLink!.sendRequest(request, options);
909 const lockedUntilUtc = new Date(result.body.expiration);
910 log.mgmt(
911 "[%s] Lock for session '%s' will expire at %s.",
912 this._context.namespace.connectionId,
913 sessionId,
914 lockedUntilUtc.toString()
915 );
916 return lockedUntilUtc;
917 } catch (err) {
918 const error = translate(err);
919 log.error(
920 "An error occurred while sending the renew lock request to $management " + "endpoint: %O",
921 error
922 );
923 throw error;
924 }
925 }

1021 /**
1022 * Lists the sessions on the ServiceBus Queue/Topic.
1023 * @param lastUpdateTime Filter to include only sessions updated after a given time.
1024 * @param skip The number of sessions to skip
1025 * @param top Maximum numer of sessions.
1026 * @returns Promise<string[]> A list of session ids.
1027 */
1028 async listMessageSessions(skip: number, top: number, lastUpdatedTime?: Date): Promise<string[]> {
1029 throwErrorIfConnectionClosed(this._context.namespace);
1030 const defaultLastUpdatedTimeForListingSessions: number = 259200000; // 3 * 24 * 3600 * 1000
1031 if (typeof skip !== "number") {
1032 throw new Error("'skip' is a required parameter and must be of type 'number'.");
1033 }
1034 if (typeof top !== "number") {
1035 throw new Error("'top' is a required parameter and must be of type 'number'.");
1036 }
1037 if (lastUpdatedTime && !(lastUpdatedTime instanceof Date)) {
1038 throw new Error("'lastUpdatedTime' must be of type 'Date'.");
1039 }
1040 if (!lastUpdatedTime) {
1041 lastUpdatedTime = new Date(Date.now() - defaultLastUpdatedTimeForListingSessions);
1042 }
1043 try {
1044 const messageBody: any = {};
1045 messageBody["last-updated-time"] = lastUpdatedTime;
1046 messageBody["skip"] = types.wrap_int(skip);
1047 messageBody["top"] = types.wrap_int(top);
1048 const request: AmqpMessage = {
1049 body: messageBody,
1050 reply_to: this.replyTo,
1051 application_properties: {
1052 operation: Constants.operations.enumerateSessions
1053 }
1054 };
1055 request.application_properties![Constants.trackingId] = generate_uuid();
1056 log.mgmt(
1057 "[%s] List sessions request body: %O.",
1058 this._context.namespace.connectionId,
1059 request.body
1060 );
1061 log.mgmt(
1062 "[%s] Acquiring lock to get the management req res link.",
1063 this._context.namespace.connectionId
1064 );
1065 await defaultLock.acquire(this.managementLock, () => {
1066 return this._init();
1067 });
1068 const response = await this._mgmtReqResLink!.sendRequest(request);
1069
1070 return (response && response.body && response.body["sessions-ids"]) || [];
1071 } catch (err) {
1072 const error = translate(err);
1073 log.error(
1074 "An error occurred while sending the renew lock request to $management " + "endpoint: %O",
1075 error
1076 );
1077 throw error;
1078 }
1079 }
1080
1081 /**
1082 * Get all the rules on the Subscription.
1083 * @returns Promise<RuleDescription[]> A list of rules.
1084 */
1085 async getRules(): Promise<RuleDescription[]> {
1086 throwErrorIfConnectionClosed(this._context.namespace);
1087 try {
1088 const request: AmqpMessage = {
1089 body: {
1090 top: types.wrap_int(max32BitNumber),
1091 skip: types.wrap_int(0)
1092 },
1093 reply_to: this.replyTo,
1094 application_properties: {
1095 operation: Constants.operations.enumerateRules
1096 }
1097 };
1098 request.application_properties![Constants.trackingId] = generate_uuid();
1099
1100 log.mgmt(
1101 "[%s] Get rules request body: %O.",
1102 this._context.namespace.connectionId,
1103 request.body
1104 );
1105 log.mgmt(
1106 "[%s] Acquiring lock to get the management req res link.",
1107 this._context.namespace.connectionId
1108 );
1109 await defaultLock.acquire(this.managementLock, () => {
1110 return this._init();
1111 });
1112
1113 const response = await this._mgmtReqResLink!.sendRequest(request);
1114 if (
1115 response.application_properties!.statusCode === 204 ||
1116 !response.body ||
1117 !Array.isArray(response.body.rules)
1118 ) {
1119 return [];
1120 }
1121
1122 // Reference: https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/service-bus-messaging/service-bus-amqp-request-response#response-11
1123 const result: { "rule-description": Typed }[] = response.body.rules || [];
1124 const rules: RuleDescription[] = [];
1125 result.forEach((x) => {
1126 const ruleDescriptor = x["rule-description"];
1127
1128 // We use the first three elements of the `ruleDescriptor.value` to get filter, action, name
1129 if (
1130 !ruleDescriptor ||
1131 !ruleDescriptor.descriptor ||
1132 ruleDescriptor.descriptor.value !== Constants.descriptorCodes.ruleDescriptionList ||
1133 !Array.isArray(ruleDescriptor.value) ||
1134 ruleDescriptor.value.length < 3
1135 ) {
1136 return;
1137 }
1138
1139 const filtersRawData: Typed = ruleDescriptor.value[0];
1140 const actionsRawData: Typed = ruleDescriptor.value[1];
1141 const rule: RuleDescription = {
1142 name: ruleDescriptor.value[2].value
1143 };
1144
1145 switch (filtersRawData.descriptor.value) {
1146 case Constants.descriptorCodes.trueFilterList:
1147 rule.filter = "1=1";
1148 break;
1149 case Constants.descriptorCodes.falseFilterList:
1150 rule.filter = "1=0";
1151 break;
1152 case Constants.descriptorCodes.sqlFilterList:
1153 rule.filter = this._safelyGetTypedValueFromArray(filtersRawData.value, 0);
1154 break;
1155 case Constants.descriptorCodes.correlationFilterList:
1156 rule.filter = {
1157 correlationId: this._safelyGetTypedValueFromArray(filtersRawData.value, 0),
1158 messageId: this._safelyGetTypedValueFromArray(filtersRawData.value, 1),
1159 to: this._safelyGetTypedValueFromArray(filtersRawData.value, 2),
1160 replyTo: this._safelyGetTypedValueFromArray(filtersRawData.value, 3),
1161 label: this._safelyGetTypedValueFromArray(filtersRawData.value, 4),
1162 sessionId: this._safelyGetTypedValueFromArray(filtersRawData.value, 5),
1163 replyToSessionId: this._safelyGetTypedValueFromArray(filtersRawData.value, 6),
1164 contentType: this._safelyGetTypedValueFromArray(filtersRawData.value, 7),
1165 userProperties: this._safelyGetTypedValueFromArray(filtersRawData.value, 8)
1166 };
1167 break;
1168 default:
1169 log.mgmt(
1170 `Found unexpected descriptor code for the filter: ${filtersRawData.descriptor.value}`
1171 );
1172 break;
1173 }
1174
1175 if (
1176 actionsRawData.descriptor.value === Constants.descriptorCodes.sqlRuleActionList &&
1177 Array.isArray(actionsRawData.value) &&
1178 actionsRawData.value.length
1179 ) {
1180 rule.action = this._safelyGetTypedValueFromArray(actionsRawData.value, 0);
1181 }
1182
1183 rules.push(rule);
1184 });
1185
1186 return rules;
1187 } catch (err) {
1188 const error = translate(err);
1189 log.error(
1190 "An error occurred while sending the get rules request to $management " + "endpoint: %O",
1191 error
1192 );
1193 throw error;
1194 }
1195 }
1196

1201 async removeRule(ruleName: string): Promise<void> {

1204 ruleName = String(ruleName);
1205 throwTypeErrorIfParameterIsEmptyString(
1206 this._context.namespace.connectionId,
1207 "ruleName",
1208 ruleName

1212 const request: AmqpMessage = {

1222

1224 "[%s] Remove Rule request body: %O.",

1241 error

1246
1247 /**
1248 * Adds a rule on the subscription as defined by the given rule name, filter and action
1249 * @param ruleName Name of the rule
1250 * @param filter A Boolean, SQL expression or a Correlation filter
1251 * @param sqlRuleActionExpression Action to perform if the message satisfies the filtering expression
1252 */
1253 async addRule(
1254 ruleName: string,
1255 filter: boolean | string | CorrelationFilter,
1256 sqlRuleActionExpression?: string
1257 ): Promise<void> {
1258 throwErrorIfConnectionClosed(this._context.namespace);
1259
1260 throwTypeErrorIfParameterMissing(this._context.namespace.connectionId, "ruleName", ruleName);
1261 ruleName = String(ruleName);
1262 throwTypeErrorIfParameterIsEmptyString(
1263 this._context.namespace.connectionId,
1264 "ruleName",
1265 ruleName
1266 );
1267
1268 throwTypeErrorIfParameterMissing(this._context.namespace.connectionId, "filter", filter);
1269 if (
1270 typeof filter !== "boolean" &&
1271 typeof filter !== "string" &&
1272 !correlationProperties.some((validProperty) => filter.hasOwnProperty(validProperty))
1273 ) {
1274 throw new TypeError(
1275 `The parameter "filter" should be either a boolean, string or implement the CorrelationFilter interface.`
1276 );
1277 }
1278
1279 try {
1280 const ruleDescription: any = {};
1281 switch (typeof filter) {
1282 case "boolean":
1283 ruleDescription["sql-filter"] = {
1284 expression: filter ? "1=1" : "1=0"
1285 };
1286 break;
1287 case "string":
1288 ruleDescription["sql-filter"] = {
1289 expression: filter
1290 };
1291 break;
1292 default:
1293 ruleDescription["correlation-filter"] = {
1294 "correlation-id": filter.correlationId,
1295 "message-id": filter.messageId,
1296 to: filter.to,
1297 "reply-to": filter.replyTo,
1298 label: filter.label,
1299 "session-id": filter.sessionId,
1300 "reply-to-session-id": filter.replyToSessionId,
1301 "content-type": filter.contentType,
1302 properties: filter.userProperties
1303 };
1304 break;
1305 }
1306
1307 if (sqlRuleActionExpression !== undefined) {
1308 ruleDescription["sql-rule-action"] = {
1309 expression: String(sqlRuleActionExpression)
1310 };
1311 }
1312 const request: AmqpMessage = {
1313 body: {
1314 "rule-name": types.wrap_string(ruleName),
1315 "rule-description": types.wrap_map(ruleDescription)
1316 },
1317 reply_to: this.replyTo,
1318 application_properties: {
1319 operation: Constants.operations.addRule
1320 }
1321 };
1322 request.application_properties![Constants.trackingId] = generate_uuid();
1323
1324 log.mgmt(
1325 "[%s] Add Rule request body: %O.",
1326 this._context.namespace.connectionId,
1327 request.body
1328 );
1329 log.mgmt(
1330 "[%s] Acquiring lock to get the management req res link.",
1331 this._context.namespace.connectionId
1332 );

1337 await this._mgmtReqResLink!.sendRequest(request);

1345 }

731 onError: this._onAmqpError,
732 onSessionError: this._onSessionError,
733 onSettled: this._onSettled
734 };
735 }
736 const rcvrOptions: ReceiverOptions = {
737 name: useNewName ? getUniqueName(this._context.entityPath) : this.name,
738 autoaccept: this.receiveMode === ReceiveMode.receiveAndDelete ? true : false,
739 // receiveAndDelete -> first(0), peekLock -> second (1)
740 rcv_settle_mode: this.receiveMode === ReceiveMode.receiveAndDelete ? 0 : 1,
741 // receiveAndDelete -> settled (1), peekLock -> unsettled (0)
742 snd_settle_mode: this.receiveMode === ReceiveMode.receiveAndDelete ? 1 : 0,
743 source: {
744 address: this.address
745 },
746 credit_window: 0,
747 ...options
748 };
749
750 return rcvrOptions;

753 /**
754 * Creates a new AMQP receiver under a new AMQP session.
755 * @protected
756 *
757 * @returns {Promise<void>} Promise<void>.

759 protected async _init(options?: ReceiverOptions): Promise<void> {
760 const connectionId = this._context.namespace.connectionId;
761 try {
762 if (!this.isOpen() && !this.isConnecting) {
763 log.error(

765 "establishing itself. Hence let's try to connect.",
766 connectionId,
767 this.name,
768 this.address
769 );
770 this.isConnecting = true;
771 await this._negotiateClaim();
772 if (!options) {
773 options = this._createReceiverOptions();
774 }
775 log.error(

777 connectionId,
778 this.name,
779 options
780 );
781
782 this._receiver = await this._context.namespace.connection.createReceiver(options);
783 this.isConnecting = false;

786 connectionId,
787 this.name,
788 this.address
789 );
790 log[this.receiverType](
791 "Promise to create the receiver resolved. " + "Created receiver with name: ",
792 this.name
793 );
794 log[this.receiverType](
795 "[%s] Receiver '%s' created with receiver options: %O",
796 connectionId,
797 this.name,
798 options
799 );
800 // It is possible for someone to close the receiver and then start it again.
801 // Thus make sure that the receiver is present in the client cache.
802 if (this.receiverType === ReceiverType.streaming && !this._context.streamingReceiver) {
803 this._context.streamingReceiver = this as any;
804 } else if (this.receiverType === ReceiverType.batching && !this._context.batchingReceiver) {
805 this._context.batchingReceiver = this as any;
806 }
807 await this._ensureTokenRenewal();
808 } else {
809 log.error(
810 "[%s] The receiver '%s' with address '%s' is open -> %s and is connecting " +
811 "-> %s. Hence not reconnecting.",
812 connectionId,
813 this.name,
814 this.address,
815 this.isOpen(),
816 this.isConnecting
817 );
818 }
819 } catch (err) {
820 this.isConnecting = false;
Error Row 821, Column 7: "Do not assign to the exception parameter." no-ex-assign
821 err = translate(err);
822 log.error(
823 "[%s] An error occured while creating the receiver '%s': %O",
824 this._context.namespace.connectionId,
825 this.name,
826 err
827 );
828 throw err;
829 }

832 protected _deleteFromCache(): void {
833 this._receiver = undefined;
834 if (this.receiverType === ReceiverType.streaming) {
835 this._context.streamingReceiver = undefined;
836 } else if (this.receiverType === ReceiverType.batching) {
837 this._context.batchingReceiver = undefined;
838 }
839 log.error(
840 "[%s] Deleted the receiver '%s' from the client cache.",
841 this._context.namespace.connectionId,

846 /**
847 * Will reconnect the receiver link if necessary.
848 * @param {AmqpError | Error} [receiverError] The receiver error if any.
849 * @returns {Promise<void>} Promise<void>.
850 */
851 async onDetached(receiverError?: AmqpError | Error): Promise<void> {
852 const connectionId = this._context.namespace.connectionId;
853 try {
854 // Local 'wasCloseInitiated' serves same purpose as {this.wasCloseInitiated}
855 // but the condition is inferred based on state of receiver in context of network disconnect scenario
856 const wasCloseInitiated = this._receiver && this._receiver.isItselfClosed();
857 // Clears the token renewal timer. Closes the link and its session if they are open.
858 // Removes the link and its session if they are present in rhea's cache.
859 await this._closeLink(this._receiver);
860
861 if (this.receiverType === ReceiverType.batching) {
862 log.error(
863 "[%s] Receiver '%s' with address '%s' is a Batching Receiver, so we will not be " +
864 "re-establishing the receiver link.",
865 connectionId,
866 this.name,
867 this.address
868 );
869 return;
870 }
871
872 // We should attempt to reopen only when the receiver(sdk) did not initiate the close
873 let shouldReopen = false;
874 if (receiverError && !wasCloseInitiated) {
875 const translatedError = translate(receiverError);
876 if (translatedError.retryable) {
877 shouldReopen = true;
878 log.error(
879 "[%s] close() method of Receiver '%s' with address '%s' was not called. There " +
880 "was an accompanying error and it is retryable. This is a candidate for re-establishing " +
881 "the receiver link.",
882 connectionId,
883 this.name,
884 this.address
885 );
886 } else {
887 log.error(
888 "[%s] close() method of Receiver '%s' with address '%s' was not called. There " +
889 "was an accompanying error and it is NOT retryable. Hence NOT re-establishing " +
890 "the receiver link.",
891 connectionId,
892 this.name,
893 this.address
894 );
895 }
896 } else if (!wasCloseInitiated) {
897 shouldReopen = true;
898 log.error(
899 "[%s] close() method of Receiver '%s' with address '%s' was not called. " +
900 "There was no accompanying error as well. This is a candidate for re-establishing " +
901 "the receiver link.",
902 connectionId,
903 this.name,
904 this.address
905 );
906 } else {
907 const state: any = {
908 wasCloseInitiated: wasCloseInitiated,
909 receiverError: receiverError,
910 _receiver: this._receiver
911 };
912 log.error(
913 "[%s] Something went wrong. State of Receiver '%s' with address '%s' is: %O",
914 connectionId,
915 this.name,
916 this.address,
917 state
918 );
919 }
920 if (shouldReopen) {
921 const disconnectedReceiverName = this.name;
922 // provide a new name to the link while re-connecting it. This ensures that
923 // the service does not send an error stating that the link is still open.
924 const options: ReceiverOptions = this._createReceiverOptions(true);
925
926 this.name = options.name!;
927
928 log.receiver(
929 "[%s] Closing the disconnected Receiver '%s' and creating a new one with the name '%s'",
930 this._context.namespace.connectionId,
931 disconnectedReceiverName,
932 this.name
933 );
934
935 // shall retry forever at an interval of 15 seconds if the error is a retryable error
936 // else bail out when the error is not retryable or the oepration succeeds.
937 const config: RetryConfig<void> = {
938 operation: () =>
939 this._init(options).then(async () => {
940 if (this.wasCloseInitiated) {
941 log.error(
942 "[%s] close() method of Receiver '%s' with address '%s' was called. " +
943 "by the time the receiver finished getting created. Hence, disallowing messages from being received. ",
944 connectionId,
945 this.name,
946 this.address
947 );
948 await this.close();
949 } else {
950 if (this._receiver && this.receiverType === ReceiverType.streaming) {
951 this._receiver.addCredit(this.maxConcurrentCalls);
952 }
953 }
954 return;
955 }),
956 connectionId: connectionId,
957 operationType: RetryOperationType.receiverLink,
958 times: Constants.defaultConnectionRetryAttempts,
959 connectionHost: this._context.namespace.config.host,
960 delayInSeconds: 15
961 };
962 if (!this.wasCloseInitiated) {
963 await retry<void>(config);
964 }
965 }
966 } catch (err) {
967 log.error(
968 "[%s] An error occurred while processing detached() of Receiver '%s': %O ",
969 connectionId,
970 this.name,
971 this.address,
972 err
973 );
974 }
975 }

978 * Closes the underlying AMQP receiver.

981 async close(): Promise<void> {
982 this.wasCloseInitiated = true;

985 this._context.namespace.connectionId,

470 /**
471 * Will reconnect the sender link if necessary.
472 * @param {AmqpError | Error} [senderError] The sender error if any.
473 * @returns {Promise<void>} Promise<void>.

475 async onDetached(senderError?: AmqpError | Error): Promise<void> {

479 // Removes the link and its session if they are present in rhea's cache.

514 );

523 this._context.namespace.connectionId,

646 /**
647 * Send a batch of Message to the ServiceBus in a single AMQP message. The "message_annotations",
648 * "application_properties" and "properties" of the first message will be set as that
649 * of the envelope (batch message).
650 * @param {Array<Message>} inputMessages An array of Message objects to be sent in a
651 * Batch message.
652 * @return {Promise<void>}
653 */
654 async sendBatch(inputMessages: SendableMessageInfo[]): Promise<void> {
655 throwErrorIfConnectionClosed(this._context.namespace);
656 try {
657 if (!Array.isArray(inputMessages)) {
658 inputMessages = [inputMessages];
659 }
660

678 const encodedMessages = [];

682 amqpMessage.body = this._context.namespace.dataTransformer.encode(inputMessages[i].body);
683 amqpMessages[i] = amqpMessage;
684 try {
685 encodedMessages[i] = RheaMessageUtil.encode(amqpMessage);
686 } catch (error) {
687 if (error instanceof TypeError || error.name === "TypeError") {
688 throw getMessagePropertyTypeMismatchError(inputMessages[i]) || error;
689 }
690 throw error;
691 }

693

695 const batchMessage: AmqpMessage = {
696 body: RheaMessageUtil.data_sections(encodedMessages)
697 };
698 // Set message_annotations, application_properties and properties of the first message as
699 // that of the envelope (batch message).
700 if (amqpMessages[0].message_annotations) {
701 batchMessage.message_annotations = amqpMessages[0].message_annotations;
702 }
703 if (amqpMessages[0].application_properties) {
704 batchMessage.application_properties = amqpMessages[0].application_properties;
705 }
706 for (const prop of messageProperties) {
707 if ((amqpMessages[0] as any)[prop]) {
708 (batchMessage as any)[prop] = (amqpMessages[0] as any)[prop];
709 }
710 }
711
712 // Finally encode the envelope (batch message).
713 const encodedBatchMessage = RheaMessageUtil.encode(batchMessage);
714 log.sender(
715 "[%s]Sender '%s', sending encoded batch message.",
716 this._context.namespace.connectionId,
717 this.name,
718 encodedBatchMessage
719 );
720 return await this._trySend(encodedBatchMessage, true);
721 } catch (err) {
722 log.error(
723 "[%s] Sender '%s': An error occurred while sending the messages: %O\nError: %O",
724 this._context.namespace.connectionId,
725 this.name,

727 err
728 );

206 * receive operation.

295 /**
296 * Closes the underlying AMQP receiver link.
297 * Once closed, the receiver cannot be used for any further operations.
298 * Use the `createReceiver` function on the QueueClient or SubscriptionClient to instantiate
299 * a new Receiver
300 *
301 * @returns {Promise<void>}
302 */
303 async close(): Promise<void> {
304 try {
305 this._isClosed = true;
306 if (this._context.namespace.connection && this._context.namespace.connection.isOpen()) {
307 // Close the streaming receiver.
308 if (this._context.streamingReceiver) {
309 await this._context.streamingReceiver.close();
310 }
311
312 // Close the batching receiver.
313 if (this._context.batchingReceiver) {
314 await this._context.batchingReceiver.close();
315 }
316
317 // Make sure that we clear the map of deferred messages
318 this._context.requestResponseLockedMessages.clear();
319 }
320 } catch (err) {
321 log.error(
322 "[%s] An error occurred while closing the Receiver for %s: %O",
323 this._context.namespace.connectionId,
324 this._context.entityPath,
325 err
326 );
327 throw err;
328 }
329 }
330
331 /**
332 * Indicates whether the receiver is currently receiving messages or not.
333 * When this returns true, new `registerMessageHandler()` or `receiveMessages()` calls cannot be made.
334 */
335 isReceivingMessages(): boolean {
336 if (this._context.streamingReceiver && this._context.streamingReceiver.isOpen()) {
337 return true;
338 }
339 if (
340 this._context.batchingReceiver &&
341 this._context.batchingReceiver.isOpen() &&
342 this._context.batchingReceiver.isReceivingMessages
343 ) {
344 return true;
345 }
346 return false;
347 }
348 }

680 /**
681 * Registers handlers to deal with the incoming stream of messages over an AMQP receiver link
682 * from a Queue/Subscription.
683 * To stop receiving messages, call `close()` on the SessionReceiver.
684 *
685 * Throws an error if there is another receive operation in progress on the same receiver. If you
686 * are not sure whether there is another receive operation running, check the `isReceivingMessages`
687 * property on the receiver.
688 *
689 * @param onMessage - Handler for processing each incoming message.
690 * @param onError - Handler for any error that occurs while receiving or processing messages.
691 * @param options - Options to control whether messages should be automatically completed
692 * or if the lock on the session should be automatically renewed. You can control the
693 * maximum number of messages that should be concurrently processed. You can
694 * also provide a timeout in seconds to denote the amount of time to wait for a new message
695 * before closing the receiver.
696 *
697 * @returns void
698 */
699 registerMessageHandler(
700 onMessage: OnMessage,
701 onError: OnError,
702 options?: SessionMessageHandlerOptions
703 ): void {
704 this._throwIfReceiverOrConnectionClosed();
705 this._throwIfAlreadyReceiving();
706 const connId = this._context.namespace.connectionId;
707 throwTypeErrorIfParameterMissing(connId, "onMessage", onMessage);
708 throwTypeErrorIfParameterMissing(connId, "onError", onError);
709 if (typeof onMessage !== "function") {
710 throw new TypeError("The parameter 'onMessage' must be of type 'function'.");
711 }
712 if (typeof onError !== "function") {
713 throw new TypeError("The parameter 'onError' must be of type 'function'.");
714 }
715
716 this._createMessageSessionIfDoesntExist()
717 .then(async () => {
718 if (!this._messageSession) {
719 return;
720 }
721 if (!this._isClosed) {
722 this._messageSession.receive(onMessage, onError, options);
723 } else {
724 await this._messageSession.close();
725 }
726 return;
727 })
728 .catch((err) => {
729 onError(err);
730 });

742 async *getMessageIterator(): AsyncIterableIterator<ServiceBusMessage> {

231 /**

233 * Once closed, the sender cannot be used for any further operations.
234 * Use the `createSender` function on the QueueClient or TopicClient to instantiate a new Sender
235 *
236 * @returns {Promise<void>}
237 */
238 async close(): Promise<void> {
239 try {
240 this._isClosed = true;
241 if (
242 this._context.namespace.connection &&
243 this._context.namespace.connection.isOpen() &&
244 this._context.sender
245 ) {
246 await this._context.sender.close();
247 }
248 } catch (err) {
249 log.error(
250 "[%s] An error occurred while closing the Sender for %s: %O",
251 this._context.namespace.connectionId,
252 this._context.entityPath,
253 err
254 );
255 throw err;
256 }

26 * to be fetched by the next receive operation.
27 * @type {Number}
28 */
29 peekLock = 1,
30
31 /**
32 * Messages received in this mode get automatically removed from Service Bus.
33 * @type {Number}
34 */
35 receiveAndDelete = 2
36 }

131 /**
132 * Describes the message to be sent to Service Bus.
133 * @interface SendableMessageInfo.

135 export interface SendableMessageInfo {
136 /**
137 * @property The message body that needs to be sent or is received.
138 */
139 body: any;
140 /**
141 * @property The message identifier is an
142 * application-defined value that uniquely identifies the message and its payload.
143 *
144 * Note: Numbers that are not whole integers are not allowed.
145 */
146 messageId?: string | number | Buffer;
147 /**
148 * @property The content type of the message. Optionally describes
149 * the payload of the message, with a descriptor following the format of RFC2045, Section 5, for
150 * example "application/json".
151 */
152 contentType?: string;
153 /**
154 * @property The correlation identifier that allows an
155 * application to specify a context for the message for the purposes of correlation, for example
156 * reflecting the MessageId of a message that is being replied to.
157 * See {@link https://docs.microsoft.com/azure/service-bus-messaging/service-bus-messages-payloads?#message-routing-and-correlation Message Routing and Correlation}.
158 */
159 correlationId?: string | number | Buffer;
160 /**
161 * @property The partition key for sending a message to a partitioned entity.
162 * Maximum length is 128 characters. For {@link https://docs.microsoft.com/azure/service-bus-messaging/service-bus-partitioning partitioned entities},
163 * setting this value enables assigning related messages to the same internal partition,
164 * so that submission sequence order is correctly recorded. The partition is chosen by a hash
165 * function over this value and cannot be chosen directly.
166 * - For session-aware entities, the `sessionId` property overrides this value.
167 * - For non partitioned entities, partition key will be ignored
168 *
169 */
170 partitionKey?: string;
171 /**
172 * @property The partition key for sending a message into an entity
173 * via a partitioned transfer queue. Maximum length is 128 characters. If a message is sent via a
174 * transfer queue in the scope of a transaction, this value selects the transfer queue partition:
175 * This is functionally equivalent to `partitionKey` property and ensures that messages are kept
176 * together and in order as they are transferred.
177 * See {@link https://docs.microsoft.com/azure/service-bus-messaging/service-bus-transactions#transfers-and-send-via Transfers and Send Via}.
178 */
179 viaPartitionKey?: string;
180 /**
181 * @property The session identifier for a session-aware entity. Maximum
182 * length is 128 characters. For session-aware entities, this application-defined value specifies
183 * the session affiliation of the message. Messages with the same session identifier are subject
184 * to summary locking and enable exact in-order processing and demultiplexing. For
185 * session-unaware entities, this value is ignored.
186 * {@link https://docs.microsoft.com/azure/service-bus-messaging/message-sessions Message Sessions}.
187 */
188 sessionId?: string;
189 /**
190 * @property The session identifier augmenting the `replyTo` address.
191 * Maximum length is 128 characters. This value augments the ReplyTo information and specifies
192 * which SessionId should be set for the reply when sent to the reply entity.
193 * See {@link https://docs.microsoft.com/azure/service-bus-messaging/service-bus-messages-payloads?#message-routing-and-correlation Message Routing and Correlation}.
194 */
195 replyToSessionId?: string;
196 /**
197 * @property The message‚Äôs time to live value. This value is the relative
198 * duration after which the message expires, starting from the instant the message has been
199 * accepted and stored by the broker, as captured in `enqueuedTimeUtc`. When not set explicitly,
200 * the assumed value is the DefaultTimeToLive for the respective queue or topic. A message-level
201 * `timeToLive` value cannot be longer than the entity's DefaultTimeToLive setting and it is
202 * silently adjusted if it does. See
203 * {@link https://docs.microsoft.com/azure/service-bus-messaging/message-expiration Expiration}.
204 */
205 timeToLive?: number;
206 /**
207 * @property The application specific label. This property enables the
208 * application to indicate the purpose of the message to the receiver in a standardized. fashion,
209 * similar to an email subject line. The mapped AMQP property is "subject".
210 */
211 label?: string;
212 /**
213 * @property The "to" address. This property is reserved for future use in routing
214 * scenarios and presently ignored by the broker itself. Applications can use this value in
215 * rule-driven {@link https://docs.microsoft.com/azure/service-bus-messaging/service-bus-auto-forwarding auto-forward chaining}
216 * scenarios to indicate the intended logical destination of the message.
217 */
218 to?: string;
219 /**
220 * @property The address of an entity to send replies to. This optional and
221 * application-defined value is a standard way to express a reply path to the receiver of the
222 * message. When a sender expects a reply, it sets the value to the absolute or relative path of
223 * the queue or topic it expects the reply to be sent to. See
224 * {@link https://docs.microsoft.com/azure/service-bus-messaging/service-bus-messages-payloads?#message-routing-and-correlation Message Routing and Correlation}.
225 */
226 replyTo?: string;
227 /**
228 * @property The date and time in UTC at which the message will
229 * be enqueued. This property returns the time in UTC; when setting the property, the
230 * supplied DateTime value must also be in UTC. This value is for delayed message sending.
231 * It is utilized to delay messages sending to a specific time in the future. Message enqueuing
232 * time does not mean that the message will be sent at the same time. It will get enqueued,
233 * but the actual sending time depends on the queue's workload and its state.
234 */
235 scheduledEnqueueTimeUtc?: Date;
236 /**
237 * @property The application specific properties which can be
238 * used for custom message metadata.
239 */
240 userProperties?: { [key: string]: any };
241 }

306 body: msg.body,
307 message_annotations: {}
308 };
309 if (msg.userProperties != null) {
310 amqpMsg.application_properties = msg.userProperties;
311 }
312 if (msg.contentType != null) {
313 amqpMsg.content_type = msg.contentType;
314 }
315 if (msg.sessionId != null) {
316 if (msg.sessionId.length > Constants.maxSessionIdLength) {
317 throw new Error(
318 "Length of 'sessionId' property on the message cannot be greater than 128 characters."
319 );
320 }
321 amqpMsg.group_id = msg.sessionId;
322 }
323 if (msg.replyTo != null) {
324 amqpMsg.reply_to = msg.replyTo;
325 }
326 if (msg.to != null) {
327 amqpMsg.to = msg.to;
328 }
329 if (msg.label != null) {
330 amqpMsg.subject = msg.label;
331 }
332 if (msg.messageId != null) {
333 if (typeof msg.messageId === "string" && msg.messageId.length > Constants.maxMessageIdLength) {
334 throw new Error(
335 "Length of 'messageId' property on the message cannot be greater than 128 characters."
336 );
337 }
338 amqpMsg.message_id = msg.messageId;
339 }
340 if (msg.correlationId != null) {
341 amqpMsg.correlation_id = msg.correlationId;
342 }
343 if (msg.replyToSessionId != null) {
344 amqpMsg.reply_to_group_id = msg.replyToSessionId;
345 }
346 if (msg.timeToLive != null && msg.timeToLive !== Constants.maxDurationValue) {
347 amqpMsg.ttl = msg.timeToLive;
348 amqpMsg.creation_time = Date.now();
349 if (Constants.maxAbsoluteExpiryTime - amqpMsg.creation_time > amqpMsg.ttl) {
350 amqpMsg.absolute_expiry_time = amqpMsg.creation_time + amqpMsg.ttl;
351 } else {
352 amqpMsg.absolute_expiry_time = Constants.maxAbsoluteExpiryTime;
353 }
354 }
355 if (msg.partitionKey != null) {
356 if (msg.partitionKey.length > Constants.maxPartitionKeyLength) {
357 throw new Error(
358 "Length of 'partitionKey' property on the message cannot be greater than 128 characters."
359 );
360 }
361 amqpMsg.message_annotations![Constants.partitionKey] = msg.partitionKey;
362 }
363 if (msg.viaPartitionKey != null) {
364 if (msg.viaPartitionKey.length > Constants.maxPartitionKeyLength) {
365 throw new Error(
366 "Length of 'viaPartitionKey' property on the message cannot be greater than 128 characters."
367 );
368 }
369 amqpMsg.message_annotations![Constants.viaPartitionKey] = msg.viaPartitionKey;
370 }
371 if (msg.scheduledEnqueueTimeUtc != null) {
372 amqpMsg.message_annotations![Constants.scheduledEnqueueTime] = msg.scheduledEnqueueTimeUtc;
373 }
374 log.message("SBMessage to AmqpMessage: %O", amqpMsg);
375 return amqpMsg;

378 /**
379 * Describes the message received from Service Bus during peek operations and so cannot be settled.

382 export interface ReceivedMessageInfo extends SendableMessageInfo {
383 /**
384 * @property The lock token is a reference to the lock that is being held by the broker in
385 * `ReceiveMode.PeekLock` mode. Locks are used internally settle messages as explained in the
386 * {@link https://docs.microsoft.com/azure/service-bus-messaging/message-transfers-locks-settlement product documentation in more detail}
387 * - Not applicable when the message is received in `ReceiveMode.receiveAndDelete`
388 * mode.
389 * @readonly
390 */
391 readonly lockToken?: string;
392 /**
393 * @property Number of deliveries that have been attempted for this message. The count is
394 * incremented when a message lock expires, or the message is explicitly abandoned using the
395 * `abandon()` method on the message.
396 * @readonly

399 /**
400 * @property The UTC instant at which the message has been accepted and stored in Service Bus.

405 * @property The UTC instant at which the message is marked for removal and no longer available for
406 * retrieval from the entity due to expiration. This property is computed from 2 other properties
407 * on the message: `enqueuedTimeUtc` + `timeToLive`.
408 */
409 readonly expiresAtUtc?: Date;
410 /**
411 * @property The UTC instant until which the message is held locked in the queue/subscription.
412 * When the lock expires, the `deliveryCount` is incremented and the message is again available

415 * mode.
416 */

420 * messages that have been auto-forwarded, this property reflects the sequence number that had
421 * first been assigned to the message at its original point of submission.
422 * @readonly
423 */
424 readonly enqueuedSequenceNumber?: number;
425 /**
426 * @property The unique number assigned to a message by Service Bus.
427 * The sequence number is a unique 64-bit integer assigned to a message as it is accepted
428 * and stored by the broker and functions as its true identifier. For partitioned entities,
429 * the topmost 16 bits reflect the partition identifier. Sequence numbers monotonically increase.
430 * They roll over to 0 when the 48-64 bit range is exhausted.
431 *
432 * **Max safe integer** that Javascript currently supports is `2^53 - 1`. The sequence number
433 * is an AMQP `Long` type which can be upto 64 bits long. To represent that we are using a
434 * library named {@link https://github.com/dcodeIO/long.js long.js}. We expect customers
435 * to use the **`Long`** type exported by this library.
436 * @readonly
437 */
438 readonly sequenceNumber?: Long;
439 /**
440 * @property {string} [deadLetterSource] The name of the queue or subscription that this message
441 * was enqueued on, before it was deadlettered. Only set in messages that have been dead-lettered
442 * and subsequently auto-forwarded from the dead-letter queue to another entity. Indicates the
443 * entity in which the message was dead-lettered.
444 * @readonly
445 */
446 readonly deadLetterSource?: string;
447 /**
448 * @property {AmqpMessage} _amqpMessage The underlying raw amqp message.
449 * @readonly
450 */

815 /**
816 * Removes the message from Service Bus.
817 *
818 * - Throws `SessionLockLostError` (for messages from a Queue/Subscription with sessions enabled)
819 * if the AMQP link with which the message was received is no longer alive. This can
820 * happen either because the lock on the session expired or the receiver was explicitly closed by
821 * the user or the AMQP link got closed by the library due to network loss or service error.
822 * - Throws `MessageLockLostError` (for messages from a Queue/Subscription with sessions not enabled)
823 * if the lock on the message has expired or the AMQP link with which the message was received is
824 * no longer alive. The latter can happen if the receiver was explicitly closed by the user or the
825 * AMQP link got closed by the library due to network loss or service error.
826 * - Throws an error if the message is already settled. To avoid this error check the `isSettled`
827 * property on the message if you are not sure whether the message is settled.
828 * - Throws an error if used in `ReceiveAndDelete` mode because all messages received in this mode
829 * are pre-settled. To avoid this error, update your code to not settle a message which is received
830 * in this mode.
831 * - Throws `ServiceUnavailableError` if Service Bus does not acknowledge the request to settle
832 * the message in time. The message may or may not have been settled successfully.

839 this._context.namespace.connectionId,
840 this.messageId
841 );

843 await this._context.managementClient!.updateDispositionStatus(
844 this.lockToken!,
845 DispositionStatus.completed,
846 getAssociatedReceiverName(this._context, this.sessionId),
847 {
848 sessionId: this.sessionId
849 }
850 );
851
852 // Remove the message from the internal map of deferred messages
853 this._context.requestResponseLockedMessages.delete(this.lockToken!);
854 return;
855 }
856 const receiver = this._context.getReceiver(this.delivery.link.name, this.sessionId);
857 throwIfMessageCannotBeSettled(
858 receiver,
859 DispositionType.complete,
860 this.delivery.remote_settled,
861 this.sessionId
862 );

1073 /**

1075 * Logs and Throws an error if the given message cannot be settled.
1076 * @param receiver Receiver to be used to settle this message
1077 * @param operation Settle operation: complete, abandon, defer or deadLetter
1078 * @param isRemoteSettled Boolean indicating if the message has been settled at the remote
1079 * @param sessionId sessionId of the message if applicable
1080 */
1081 export function throwIfMessageCannotBeSettled(
1082 receiver: MessageReceiver | MessageSession | undefined,
1083 operation: DispositionType,
1084 isRemoteSettled: boolean,
1085 sessionId?: string
1086 ): void {
1087 let error: Error | undefined;
1088

1090 error = new Error(
1091 getErrorMessageNotSupportedInReceiveAndDeleteMode(`${operation} the message`)
1092 );
1093 } else if (isRemoteSettled) {
1094 error = new Error(`Failed to ${operation} the message as this message is already settled.`);
1095 } else if (!receiver || !receiver.isOpen()) {
1096 const errorMessage =
1097 `Failed to ${operation} the message as the AMQP link with which the message was ` +
1098 `received is no longer alive.`;

1106 description: errorMessage,
1107 condition: ErrorNameConditionMapper.MessageLockLostError
1108 });
1109 }
1110 }
1111 if (!error) {
1112 return;
1113 }
1114 if (receiver) {

78 * Queue/Subscription which has sessions enabled.
79 */
80 export interface SessionMessageHandlerOptions {
81 /**
82 * @property Indicates whether the `complete()` method on the message should automatically be
83 * called by the sdk after the user provided onMessage handler has been executed.
84 * Calling `complete()` on a message removes it from the Queue/Subscription.
85 * - **Default**: `true`.
86 */
87 autoComplete?: boolean;
88 /**
89 * @property The maximum number of concurrent calls that the library
90 * can make to the user's message handler. Once this limit has been reached, more messages will
91 * not be received until atleast one of the calls to the user's message handler has completed.
92 * - **Default**: `1`.
93 */
94 maxConcurrentCalls?: number;
95 }
96 /**
97 * @internal
98 * Describes the options for creating a Session Manager.
99 */
100 export interface SessionManagerOptions extends SessionMessageHandlerOptions {
101 /**
102 * @property {number} [maxConcurrentSessions] The maximum number of sessions that the user wants to
103 * handle concurrently.
104 * - **Default**: `2000`.
105 */
106 maxConcurrentSessions?: number;
107 /**
108 * @property The maximum amount of time the receiver will wait to receive a new message. If no new
109 * message is received in this time, then the receiver will be closed.
110 *
111 * If this option is not provided, then receiver link will stay open until manually closed.
112 *
113 * **Caution**: When setting this value, take into account the time taken to process messages. Once
114 * the receiver is closed, operations like complete()/abandon()/defer()/deadletter() cannot be
115 * invoked on messages.
116 */
117 newMessageWaitTimeoutInSeconds?: number;
118 }

121 * @internal
122 * Describes all the options that can be set while instantiating a MessageSession object.
123 */
124 export type MessageSessionOptions = SessionManagerOptions &
125 SessionReceiverOptions & {
126 callee?: SessionCallee;
127 receiveMode?: ReceiveMode;
128 };

259 /**
260 * Ensures that the session lock is renewed before it expires. The lock will not be renewed for
261 * more than the configured totalAutoLockRenewDuration.
262 */
263 private _ensureSessionLockRenewal(): void {
264 if (
265 this.autoRenewLock &&
266 new Date(this._totalAutoLockRenewDuration) > this.sessionLockedUntilUtc! &&
267 Date.now() < this._totalAutoLockRenewDuration &&
268 this.isOpen()
269 ) {
270 const connectionId = this._context.namespace.connectionId;
271 const nextRenewalTimeout = calculateRenewAfterDuration(this.sessionLockedUntilUtc!);
272 this._sessionLockRenewalTimer = setTimeout(async () => {
273 try {

276 "with name '%s'.",
277 connectionId,
278 this.sessionId,
279 this.name

282 this.sessionId!,

284 {
285 delayInSeconds: 0,
286 timeoutInSeconds: 10,
287 times: 4
288 }
289 );
290 log.receiver(
291 "[%s] Successfully renewed the session lock for MessageSession '%s' " +
292 "with name '%s'.",
293 connectionId,
294 this.sessionId,
295 this.name
296 );
297 log.receiver(
298 "[%s] Calling _ensureSessionLockRenewal() again for MessageSession '%s'.",
299 connectionId,
300 this.sessionId
301 );
302 this._ensureSessionLockRenewal();
303 } catch (err) {
304 log.error(
305 "[%s] An error occurred while renewing the session lock for MessageSession " +
306 "'%s' with name '%s': %O",
307 this._context.namespace.connectionId,
308 this.sessionId,
309 this.name,
310 err
311 );
312 }
313 }, nextRenewalTimeout);
314 log.messageSession(
315 "[%s] MessageSession '%s' with name '%s', has next session lock renewal " +
316 "in %d seconds @(%s).",
317 this._context.namespace.connectionId,
318 this.sessionId,
319 this.name,
320 nextRenewalTimeout / 1000,

322 );
323 }

340 /**
341 * Creates a new AMQP receiver under a new AMQP session.
342 */
343 private async _init(): Promise<void> {
344 const connectionId = this._context.namespace.connectionId;
345 try {
346 if (!this.isOpen() && !this.isConnecting) {
347 log.error(
348 "[%s] The receiver '%s' with address '%s' is not open and is not currently " +
349 "establishing itself. Hence let's try to connect.",
350 connectionId,
351 this.name,
352 this.address
353 );
354 this.isConnecting = true;
355 await this._negotiateClaim();
356
357 const options = this._createMessageSessionOptions();
358
359 log.error(
360 "[%s] Trying to create receiver '%s' with options %O",
361 connectionId,
362 this.name,
363 options
364 );
365
366 this._receiver = await this._context.namespace.connection.createReceiver(options);
367 this.isConnecting = false;
368 const receivedSessionId =
369 this._receiver.source &&
370 this._receiver.source.filter &&
371 this._receiver.source.filter[Constants.sessionFilterName];
372 let errorMessage: string = "";
373 // SB allows a sessionId with empty string value :)
374 if (receivedSessionId == null) {
375 errorMessage =
376 `Received an incorrect sessionId '${receivedSessionId}' while creating ` +
377 `the receiver '${this.name}'.`;
378 }
379 if (this.sessionId != null && receivedSessionId !== this.sessionId) {
380 errorMessage =
381 `Received sessionId '${receivedSessionId}' does not match the provided ` +
382 `sessionId '${this.sessionId}' while creating the receiver '${this.name}'.`;
383 }
384 if (errorMessage) {
385 const error = translate({
386 description: errorMessage,
387 condition: ErrorNameConditionMapper.SessionCannotBeLockedError
388 });
389 log.error("[%s] %O", this._context.namespace.connectionId, error);
390 throw error;
391 }
392 if (this.sessionId == null) this.sessionId = receivedSessionId;
393 this.sessionLockedUntilUtc = convertTicksToDate(
394 this._receiver.properties["com.microsoft:locked-until-utc"]
395 );
396 log.messageSession(
397 "[%s] Session with id '%s' is locked until: '%s'.",
398 connectionId,
399 this.sessionId,
400 this.sessionLockedUntilUtc.toISOString()
401 );
402 log.error(
403 "[%s] Receiver '%s' for sessionId '%s' has established itself.",
404 connectionId,
405 this.name,
406 this.sessionId
407 );
408 log.messageSession(
409 "Promise to create the receiver resolved. " + "Created receiver with name: ",
410 this.name
411 );
412 log.messageSession(
413 "[%s] Receiver '%s' created with receiver options: %O",
414 connectionId,
415 this.name,
416 options
417 );
418 if (!this._context.messageSessions[this.sessionId!]) {
419 this._context.messageSessions[this.sessionId!] = this;
420 }
421 this._totalAutoLockRenewDuration = Date.now() + this.maxAutoRenewDurationInSeconds * 1000;
422 await this._ensureTokenRenewal();
423 await this._ensureSessionLockRenewal();
424 } else {
425 log.error(
426 "[%s] The receiver '%s' for sessionId '%s' is open -> %s and is connecting " +
427 "-> %s. Hence not reconnecting.",
428 connectionId,
429 this.name,
430 this.sessionId,
431 this.isOpen(),
432 this.isConnecting
433 );
434 }
435 } catch (err) {
436 this.isConnecting = false;
437 const errObj = translate(err);
438 log.error(
439 "[%s] An error occured while creating the receiver '%s': %O",
440 this._context.namespace.connectionId,
441 this.name,
442 errObj
443 );
444 throw errObj;
445 }
446 }

448 /**
449 * Creates the options that need to be specified while creating an AMQP receiver link.
450 */
451 private _createMessageSessionOptions(): ReceiverOptions {
452 const rcvrOptions: ReceiverOptions = {
453 name: this.name,
454 autoaccept: false,
455 // receiveAndDelete -> first(0), peekLock -> second (1)
456 rcv_settle_mode: this.receiveMode === ReceiveMode.receiveAndDelete ? 0 : 1,
457 // receiveAndDelete -> settled (1), peekLock -> unsettled (0)
458 snd_settle_mode: this.receiveMode === ReceiveMode.receiveAndDelete ? 1 : 0,
459 source: {
460 address: this.address,
461 filter: {}
462 },
463 credit_window: 0,
464 onClose: (context) =>
465 this._onAmqpClose(context).catch(() => {
466 /* */
467 }),
468 onSessionClose: (context) =>
469 this._onSessionClose(context).catch(() => {
470 /* */
471 }),
472 onError: this._onAmqpError,
473 onSessionError: this._onSessionError,
474 onSettled: this._onSettled
475 };
476 (rcvrOptions.source as any).filter[Constants.sessionFilterName] = this.sessionId;
477 return rcvrOptions;
478 }

688 /**
689 * Closes the underlying AMQP receiver link.

691 * This is so that the internal map of expired sessions doesn't get cleared when session is
692 * closed due to expiry.
693 */
694 async close(isClosedDueToExpiry?: boolean): Promise<void> {

698 this._context.namespace.connectionId,
699 this.sessionId,
700 this.name

724 this._context.namespace.connectionId,

746 /**
747 * Registers handlers to deal with the incoming stream of messages over an AMQP receiver link
748 * from a Queue/Subscription.
749 * To stop receiving messages, call `close()` on the SessionReceiver or set the property
750 * `newMessageWaitTimeoutInSeconds` in the options to provide a timeout.
751 *
752 * @param onMessage - Handler for processing each incoming message.
753 * @param onError - Handler for any error that occurs while receiving or processing messages.
754 * @param options - Options to control whether messages should be automatically completed. You can
755 * also provide a timeout in seconds to denote the amount of time to wait for a new message
756 * before closing the receiver.
757 *
758 * @returns void
759 */
760 receive(onMessage: OnMessage, onError: OnError, options?: SessionMessageHandlerOptions): void {
761 if (!options) options = {};
762 this.isReceivingMessages = true;
763 if (typeof options.maxConcurrentCalls === "number" && options.maxConcurrentCalls > 0) {
764 this.maxConcurrentCalls = options.maxConcurrentCalls;
765 }
766
767 // If explicitly set to false then autoComplete is false else true (default).
768 this.autoComplete = options.autoComplete === false ? options.autoComplete : true;
769 this._onMessage = onMessage;
770 this._onError = onError;
771 const connectionId = this._context.namespace.connectionId;
772
773 /**
774 * Resets the timer when a new message is received for Session Manager.
775 * It will close the receiver gracefully, if no
776 * messages were received for the configured newMessageWaitTimeoutInSeconds
777 */
778 const resetTimerOnNewMessageReceived = (): void => {
779 if (this._newMessageReceivedTimer) clearTimeout(this._newMessageReceivedTimer);
780 if (this.newMessageWaitTimeoutInSeconds) {
781 this._newMessageReceivedTimer = setTimeout(async () => {
782 const msg =
783 `MessageSession '${this.sessionId}' with name '${this.name}' did not receive ` +
784 `any messages in the last ${
785 this.newMessageWaitTimeoutInSeconds
786 } seconds. Hence closing it.`;
787 log.error("[%s] %s", this._context.namespace.connectionId, msg);
788
789 if (this.callee === SessionCallee.sessionManager) {
790 // The session manager will not forward this error to user.
791 // Instead, this is taken as a indicator to create a new session client for the next session.
792 const error = translate({
793 condition: "com.microsoft:message-wait-timeout",
794 description: msg
795 });
796 this._notifyError(translate(error));
797 }
798 await this.close();
799 }, this.newMessageWaitTimeoutInSeconds * 1000);
800 }
801 };

803 if (this._receiver && this._receiver.isOpen()) {
804 const onSessionMessage = async (context: EventContext): Promise<void> => {
805 // If the receiver got closed in PeekLock mode, avoid processing the message as we
806 // cannot settle the message.
807 if (

32 /**
33 * @internal
34 * If you try to turn a Guid into a Buffer in .NET, the bytes of the first three groups get
35 * flipped within the group, but the last two groups don't get flipped, so we end up with a
36 * different byte order. This is the order of bytes needed to make Service Bus recognize the token.
37 *
38 * @param lockToken The lock token whose bytes need to be reorded.
39 * @returns Buffer - Buffer representing reordered bytes.
40 */
41 export function reorderLockToken(lockTokenBytes: Buffer): Buffer {
42 if (!lockTokenBytes || !Buffer.isBuffer(lockTokenBytes)) {
43 return lockTokenBytes;

53 lockTokenBytes[4],

55 lockTokenBytes[7],
56 lockTokenBytes[6],
57
58 lockTokenBytes[8],
59 lockTokenBytes[9],
60
61 lockTokenBytes[10],
62 lockTokenBytes[11],
63 lockTokenBytes[12],
64 lockTokenBytes[13],
65 lockTokenBytes[14],
66 lockTokenBytes[15]

68 }

70 /**
71 * @internal
72 * Provides the time in milliseconds after which the lock renewal should occur.
73 * @param lockedUntilUtc - The time until which the message is locked.
74 */
75 export function calculateRenewAfterDuration(lockedUntilUtc: Date): number {
76 const now = Date.now();
77 const lockedUntil = lockedUntilUtc.getTime();
78 const remainingTime = lockedUntil - now;
79 log.utils("Locked until utc : %d", lockedUntil);
80 log.utils("Current time is : %d", now);
81 log.utils("Remaining time is : %d", remainingTime);
82 if (remainingTime < 1000) {
83 return 0;
84 }
85 const buffer = Math.min(remainingTime / 2, 10000); // 10 seconds
86 const renewAfter = remainingTime - buffer;
87 log.utils("Renew after : %d", renewAfter);
88 return renewAfter;
89 }
90
91 /**
92 * @internal
93 * Converts the .net ticks to a JS Date object.
94 *
95 * - The epoch for the DateTimeOffset type is `0000-01-01`, while the epoch for JS Dates is
96 * `1970-01-01`.
97 * - The DateTimeOffset ticks value for the date `1970-01-01` is `621355968000000000`.
98 * - Hence, to convert it to the JS epoch; we `subtract` the delta from the given value.
99 * - Ticks in DateTimeOffset is `1/10000000` second, while ticks in JS Date is `1/1000` second.
100 * - Thus, we `divide` the value by `10000` to convert it to JS Date ticks.
101 *
102 * @param buf Input as a Buffer
103 * @returns Date The JS Date object.
104 */
105 export function convertTicksToDate(buf: number[]): Date {
106 const epochMicroDiff: number = 621355968000000000;
107 const longValue: Long = Long.fromBytesBE(buf);
108 const timeInMS = longValue
109 .sub(epochMicroDiff)
110 .div(10000)
111 .toNumber();
112 const result = new Date(timeInMS);
113 log.utils("The converted date is: %s", result.toString());
114 return result;
115 }
116

124 return os.cpus().length;

315 describe("Test createFromAadTokenCredentials", function(): void {
316 let sbClient: ServiceBusClient;
317 let errorWasThrown: boolean = false;
318
319 const env = getEnvVars();
320 const serviceBusEndpoint = (env.SERVICEBUS_CONNECTION_STRING.match(
321 "Endpoint=sb://((.*).servicebus.windows.net)"
322 ) || "")[1];
323
324 async function testCreateFromAadTokenCredentials(host: string, tokenCreds: any): Promise<void> {
325 const testMessages = TestMessage.getSample();
326 sbClient = ServiceBusClient.createFromAadTokenCredentials(host, tokenCreds);
327 sbClient.should.be.an.instanceof(ServiceBusClient);
328 const clients = await getSenderReceiverClients(
329 sbClient,
330 TestClientType.UnpartitionedQueue,
331 TestClientType.UnpartitionedQueue
332 );
333
334 const sender = clients.senderClient.createSender();
335 const receiver = await clients.receiverClient.createReceiver(ReceiveMode.peekLock);
336 await sender.send(testMessages);
337 const msgs = await receiver.receiveMessages(1);
338
339 should.equal(Array.isArray(msgs), true, "`ReceivedMessages` is not an array");
340 should.equal(msgs[0].body, testMessages.body, "MessageBody is different than expected");
341 should.equal(msgs.length, 1, "Unexpected number of messages");
342 }
343
344 it("throws error for invalid tokenCredentials", async function(): Promise<void> {
345 await testCreateFromAadTokenCredentials(serviceBusEndpoint, "").catch((err) => {
346 errorWasThrown = true;
347 should.equal(
348 err.message,
349 "'credentials' is a required parameter and must be an instance of ApplicationTokenCredentials | UserTokenCredentials | DeviceTokenCredentials | MSITokenCredentials.",
350 "ErrorMessage is different than expected"
351 );
352 });
353 should.equal(errorWasThrown, true, "Error thrown flag must be true");
354 });
355
356 it("Coerces input to string for host in createFromAadTokenCredentials", async function(): Promise<
357 void
358 > {
359 const env = getEnvVars();
360
Error Row 361, Column 9: "'tokenCreds' is never reassigned. Use 'const' instead." prefer-const
361 let tokenCreds = await loginWithServicePrincipalSecret(
362 env.AAD_CLIENT_ID,
363 env.AAD_CLIENT_SECRET,
364 env.AAD_TENANT_ID,
365 {
366 tokenAudience: aadServiceBusAudience
367 }
368 );
369 sbClient = ServiceBusClient.createFromAadTokenCredentials(123 as any, tokenCreds);
370 should.equal(sbClient.name, "sb://123/", "Name of the namespace is different than expected");
371 });
372
373 it("sends a message to the ServiceBus entity", async function(): Promise<void> {
374 const env = getEnvVars();
375
Error Row 376, Column 9: "'tokenCreds' is never reassigned. Use 'const' instead." prefer-const
376 let tokenCreds = await loginWithServicePrincipalSecret(
377 env.AAD_CLIENT_ID,
378 env.AAD_CLIENT_SECRET,
379 env.AAD_TENANT_ID,
380 {
381 tokenAudience: aadServiceBusAudience
382 }
383 );
384 await testCreateFromAadTokenCredentials(serviceBusEndpoint, tokenCreds);
385 await sbClient.close();
386 });

389 describe("Errors after close()", function(): void {
390 let sbClient: ServiceBusClient;
391 let senderClient: QueueClient | TopicClient;
392 let receiverClient: QueueClient | SubscriptionClient;
393 let sender: Sender;
394 let receiver: Receiver | SessionReceiver;
395 let receivedMessage: ServiceBusMessage;
396
397 afterEach(() => {
398 return sbClient.close();
399 });
400
401 async function beforeEachTest(
402 senderType: TestClientType,
403 receiverType: TestClientType,
404 entityToClose: string,
405 useSessions?: boolean
406 ): Promise<void> {
407 sbClient = getServiceBusClient();
408 const clients = await getSenderReceiverClients(sbClient, senderType, receiverType);
409 senderClient = clients.senderClient;
410 receiverClient = clients.receiverClient;
411
412 await purge(receiverClient, useSessions ? TestMessage.sessionId : undefined);
413 const peekedMsgs = await receiverClient.peek();
414 const receiverEntityType = receiverClient instanceof QueueClient ? "queue" : "topic";
415 if (peekedMsgs.length) {
416 chai.assert.fail(`Please use an empty ${receiverEntityType} for integration testing`);
417 }
418
419 sender = senderClient.createSender();
420 if (useSessions) {
421 receiver = receiverClient.createReceiver(ReceiveMode.peekLock, {
422 sessionId: TestMessage.sessionId
423 });
424 } else {
425 receiver = receiverClient.createReceiver(ReceiveMode.peekLock);
426 }
427
428 // Normal send/receive
429 const testMessage = useSessions ? TestMessage.getSessionSample() : TestMessage.getSample();
430 await sender.send(testMessage);
431 const receivedMsgs = await receiver.receiveMessages(1, 3);
432 should.equal(receivedMsgs.length, 1, "Unexpected number of messages received");
433 receivedMessage = receivedMsgs[0];
434
435 // close(), so that we can then test the resulting error.
436 switch (entityToClose) {
437 case "namespace":
438 await sbClient.close();
439 break;
440 case "senderClient":
441 await senderClient.close();
442 break;
443 case "receiverClient":
444 await receiverClient.close();
445 break;
446 case "sender":
447 await sender.close();
448 break;
449 case "receiver":
450 await receiver.close();
451 break;
452 default:
453 break;
454 }
455 }
456
457 /**
458 * Tests the error from settling a message after the receiver is closed
459 */
460 async function testAllDispositions(): Promise<void> {
461 await testDisposition(DispositionType.complete);
462 await testDisposition(DispositionType.abandon);
463 await testDisposition(DispositionType.defer);
464 await testDisposition(DispositionType.deadletter);
465 }
466
467 async function testDisposition(operation: DispositionType): Promise<void> {
468 let caughtError: Error | undefined;
469 let expectedError: Error | undefined;
470
471 try {
472 switch (operation) {
473 case DispositionType.complete:
474 await receivedMessage.complete();
475 break;
476 case DispositionType.abandon:
477 await receivedMessage.abandon();
478 break;
479 case DispositionType.defer:
480 await receivedMessage.defer();
481 break;
482 case DispositionType.deadletter:
483 await receivedMessage.deadLetter();
484 break;
485
486 default:
487 break;
488 }
489 } catch (error) {
490 caughtError = error;
491 }
492
493 try {
494 throwIfMessageCannotBeSettled(
495 undefined,
496 operation,
497 receivedMessage.isSettled,
498 receivedMessage.sessionId
499 );
500 } catch (error) {
501 expectedError = error;
502 }
503
504 should.equal(caughtError && caughtError.message, expectedError && expectedError.message);
505 }
506
507 /**
508 * Tests that each feature of the sender throws expected error
509 */
510 async function testSender(expectedErrorMsg: string): Promise<void> {
511 should.equal(sender.isClosed, true, "Sender is not marked as closed.");
512
513 const testMessage = TestMessage.getSample();
514 let errorSend: string = "";
515 await sender.send(testMessage).catch((err) => {
516 errorSend = err.message;
517 });
518 should.equal(errorSend, expectedErrorMsg, "Expected error not thrown for send()");
519
520 let errorSendBatch: string = "";
521 await sender.sendBatch([testMessage]).catch((err) => {
522 errorSendBatch = err.message;
523 });
524 should.equal(errorSendBatch, expectedErrorMsg, "Expected error not thrown for sendBatch()");
525
526 let errorScheduleMsg: string = "";
527 await sender.scheduleMessage(new Date(Date.now() + 30000), testMessage).catch((err) => {
528 errorScheduleMsg = err.message;
529 });
530 should.equal(
531 errorScheduleMsg,
532 expectedErrorMsg,
533 "Expected error not thrown for scheduleMessage()"
534 );
535
536 let errorScheduleMsgs: string = "";
537 await sender.scheduleMessages(new Date(Date.now() + 30000), [testMessage]).catch((err) => {
538 errorScheduleMsgs = err.message;
539 });
540 should.equal(
541 errorScheduleMsgs,
542 expectedErrorMsg,
543 "Expected error not thrown for scheduleMessages()"
544 );
545
546 let errorCancelMsg: string = "";
547 await sender.cancelScheduledMessage(long.ZERO).catch((err) => {
548 errorCancelMsg = err.message;
549 });
550 should.equal(
551 errorCancelMsg,
552 expectedErrorMsg,
553 "Expected error not thrown for cancelScheduledMessage()"
554 );
555
556 let errorCancelMsgs: string = "";
557 await sender.cancelScheduledMessages([long.ZERO]).catch((err) => {
558 errorCancelMsgs = err.message;
559 });
560 should.equal(
561 errorCancelMsgs,
562 expectedErrorMsg,
563 "Expected error not thrown for cancelScheduledMessages()"
564 );
565 }

580 /**
581 * Tests that each feature of the receiver throws expected error
582 */
583 async function testReceiver(expectedErrorMsg: string, useSessions?: boolean): Promise<void> {
584 should.equal(receiver.isClosed, true, "Receiver is not marked as closed.");
585
586 let errorReceiveBatch: string = "";
587 await receiver.receiveMessages(1, 1).catch((err) => {
588 errorReceiveBatch = err.message;
589 });
590 should.equal(
591 errorReceiveBatch,
592 expectedErrorMsg,
593 "Expected error not thrown for receiveMessages()"
594 );
595
596 let errorReceiveStream: string = "";
597 try {
598 receiver.registerMessageHandler(() => Promise.resolve(), (e) => console.log(e));
599 } catch (err) {
600 errorReceiveStream = err.message;
601 }
602 should.equal(
603 errorReceiveStream,
604 expectedErrorMsg,
605 "Expected error not thrown for registerMessageHandler()"
606 );
607
608 let errorDeferredMsg: string = "";
609 await receiver.receiveDeferredMessage(long.ZERO).catch((err) => {
610 errorDeferredMsg = err.message;
611 });
612 should.equal(
613 errorDeferredMsg,
614 expectedErrorMsg,
615 "Expected error not thrown for receiveDeferredMessage()"
616 );
617
618 let errorDeferredMsgs: string = "";
619 await receiver.receiveDeferredMessage(long.ZERO).catch((err) => {
620 errorDeferredMsgs = err.message;
621 });
622 should.equal(
623 errorDeferredMsgs,
624 expectedErrorMsg,
625 "Expected error not thrown for receiveDeferredMessages()"
626 );
627
628 if (!useSessions) {
629 let errorRenewLock: string = "";
630 await (<Receiver>receiver).renewMessageLock("randomLockToken").catch((err) => {
631 errorRenewLock = err.message;
632 });
633 should.equal(errorRenewLock, expectedErrorMsg, "Expected error not thrown for renewLock()");
634 }
635 }

30 async function testPeekMsgsLength(
31 client: QueueClient | SubscriptionClient,
32 expectedPeekLength: number
33 ): Promise<void> {
34 const peekedMsgs = await client.peek(expectedPeekLength + 1);
35 should.equal(
36 peekedMsgs.length,
37 expectedPeekLength,
38 "Unexpected number of msgs found when peeking"
39 );
40 }

42 let sbClient: ServiceBusClient;
43
44 let senderClient: QueueClient | TopicClient;
45 let receiverClient: QueueClient | SubscriptionClient;
46 let deadLetterClient: QueueClient | SubscriptionClient;
47 let sessionReceiver: SessionReceiver;
48 let sender: Sender;
49 let errorWasThrown: boolean;
50 let unexpectedError: Error | undefined;
51
52 function unExpectedErrorHandler(err: Error): void {
53 if (err) {
54 unexpectedError = err;
55 }
56 }
57
58 async function beforeEachTest(
59 senderType: TestClientType,
60 receiverType: TestClientType,
61 receiveMode?: ReceiveMode
62 ): Promise<void> {
63 sbClient = getServiceBusClient();
64
65 const clients = await getSenderReceiverClients(sbClient, senderType, receiverType);
66 senderClient = clients.senderClient;
67 receiverClient = clients.receiverClient;
68
69 sender = senderClient.createSender();
70
71 if (receiverClient instanceof QueueClient) {
72 deadLetterClient = sbClient.createQueueClient(
73 QueueClient.getDeadLetterQueuePath(receiverClient.entityPath)
74 );
75 }
76
77 if (receiverClient instanceof SubscriptionClient) {
78 deadLetterClient = sbClient.createSubscriptionClient(
79 TopicClient.getDeadLetterTopicPath(senderClient.entityPath, receiverClient.subscriptionName),
80 receiverClient.subscriptionName
81 );
82 }
83
84 await purge(receiverClient, TestMessage.sessionId);
85 await purge(deadLetterClient);
86 const peekedMsgs = await receiverClient.peek();
87 const receiverEntityType = receiverClient instanceof QueueClient ? "queue" : "topic";
88 if (peekedMsgs.length) {
89 chai.assert.fail(`Please use an empty ${receiverEntityType} for integration testing`);
90 }
91
92 if (!receiveMode) {
93 receiveMode = ReceiveMode.peekLock;
94 }
95 sessionReceiver = <SessionReceiver>receiverClient.createReceiver(receiveMode, {
96 sessionId: TestMessage.sessionId
97 });
98
99 errorWasThrown = false;
100 unexpectedError = undefined;
101 }
102
103 async function afterEachTest(): Promise<void> {
104 await sbClient.close();
105 }

369 return msg.abandon().then(() => {
370 abandonFlag = 1;
371 if (sessionReceiver.isReceivingMessages()) {
372 return sessionReceiver.close();
373 }
Error Row 374, Column 11: "Avoid wrapping return values in Promise.resolve" promise/no-return-wrap
374 return Promise.resolve();
375 });
376 },
377 unExpectedErrorHandler,
378 { autoComplete }
379 );

385 await sessionReceiver.close();
386 }
387
388 should.equal(unexpectedError, undefined, unexpectedError && unexpectedError.message);

748 }, unExpectedErrorHandler);

766 errorMessage,
767 expectedErrorMessage,
768 "Unexpected error message for receiveMessages"
769 );
