813 describe("Sessions Streaming - Settle an already Settled message throws error", () => {
814 afterEach(async () => {
815 await afterEachTest();
816 });
817
818 const testError = (err: Error, operation: DispositionType): void => {
819 should.equal(
820 err.message,
821 `Failed to ${operation} the message as this message is already settled.`,
822 "ErrorMessage is different than expected"
823 );
824 errorWasThrown = true;
825 };
826
827 async function testSettlement(operation: DispositionType): Promise<void> {
828 const testMessage = TestMessage.getSessionSample();
829 await sender.send(testMessage);
830
831 const receivedMsgs: ServiceBusMessage[] = [];
832 sessionReceiver.registerMessageHandler((msg: ServiceBusMessage) => {
833 receivedMsgs.push(msg);
834 return Promise.resolve();
835 }, unExpectedErrorHandler);
836
837 const msgsCheck = await checkWithTimeout(
838 () => receivedMsgs.length === 1 && receivedMsgs[0].delivery.remote_settled === true
839 );
840 should.equal(
841 msgsCheck,
842 true,
843 receivedMsgs.length !== 1
844 ? `Expected 1, received ${receivedMsgs.length} messages`
845 : "Message didnt get auto-completed in time"
846 );
847 should.equal(unexpectedError, undefined, unexpectedError && unexpectedError.message);
848
849 should.equal(receivedMsgs.length, 1, "Unexpected number of messages");
850 should.equal(receivedMsgs[0].body, testMessage.body, "MessageBody is different than expected");
851 should.equal(
852 receivedMsgs[0].messageId,
853 testMessage.messageId,
854 "MessageId is different than expected"
855 );
856
857 await testPeekMsgsLength(receiverClient, 0);
858
859 if (operation === DispositionType.complete) {
860 await receivedMsgs[0].complete().catch((err) => testError(err, operation));
861 } else if (operation === DispositionType.abandon) {
862 await receivedMsgs[0].abandon().catch((err) => testError(err, operation));
863 } else if (operation === DispositionType.deadletter) {
864 await receivedMsgs[0].deadLetter().catch((err) => testError(err, operation));
865 } else if (operation === DispositionType.defer) {
866 await receivedMsgs[0].defer().catch((err) => testError(err, operation));
867 }
868
869 should.equal(errorWasThrown, true, "Error thrown flag must be true");
870 }
871
872 it("Partitioned Queue: complete() throws error(with sessions)", async function(): Promise<void> {
873 await beforeEachTest(
874 TestClientType.PartitionedQueueWithSessions,
875 TestClientType.PartitionedQueueWithSessions
876 );
877 await testSettlement(DispositionType.complete);
878 });
879
880 it("Partitioned Subscription: complete() throws error(with sessions)", async function(): Promise<
881 void
882 > {
883 await beforeEachTest(
884 TestClientType.PartitionedTopicWithSessions,
885 TestClientType.PartitionedSubscriptionWithSessions
886 );
887 await testSettlement(DispositionType.complete);
888 });
889
890 it("UnPartitioned Queue: complete() throws error(with sessions) #RunInBrowser", async function(): Promise<

1098 describe("Sessions Streaming - maxConcurrentCalls", function(): void {
1099 afterEach(async () => {
1100 await afterEachTest();
1101 });
1102
1103 async function testConcurrency(maxConcurrentCalls?: number): Promise<void> {
1104 if (
1105 typeof maxConcurrentCalls === "number" &&
1106 (maxConcurrentCalls < 1 || maxConcurrentCalls > 2)
1107 ) {
1108 chai.assert.fail(
1109 "Sorry, the tests here only support cases when maxConcurrentCalls is set to 1 or 2"
1110 );
1111 }
1112
1113 const testMessages = [TestMessage.getSessionSample(), TestMessage.getSessionSample()];
1114 await sender.sendBatch(testMessages);
1115
1116 const settledMsgs: ServiceBusMessage[] = [];
1117 const receivedMsgs: ServiceBusMessage[] = [];
1118
1119 sessionReceiver.registerMessageHandler(
1120 async (msg: ServiceBusMessage) => {
1121 if (receivedMsgs.length === 1) {
1122 if ((!maxConcurrentCalls || maxConcurrentCalls === 1) && settledMsgs.length === 0) {
1123 throw new Error(
1124 "onMessage for the second message should not have been called before the first message got settled"
1125 );
1126 }
1127 } else {
1128 if (maxConcurrentCalls === 2 && settledMsgs.length !== 0) {
1129 throw new Error(
1130 "onMessage for the second message should have been called before the first message got settled"
1131 );
1132 }
1133 }
1134
1135 receivedMsgs.push(msg);
1136 await delay(2000);
1137 await msg.complete();
1138 settledMsgs.push(msg);
1139 },
1140 unExpectedErrorHandler,
1141 maxConcurrentCalls ? { maxConcurrentCalls } : {}
1142 );
1143
1144 await checkWithTimeout(() => settledMsgs.length === 2);
1145 await sessionReceiver.close();
1146
1147 should.equal(unexpectedError, undefined, unexpectedError && unexpectedError.message);
1148 should.equal(settledMsgs.length, 2, `Expected 2, received ${settledMsgs.length} messages.`);
1149 }

1 /*
2 Test Scenario summary:
3 - Creates a single sender and a single receiver on a queue.
4 - Runs following sequence of steps in a long running loop.
5 Sends a message -> receives a message -> performs random message disposition option
6
7 The test assumes no other process is working with the queues defined in here,
8 but the queues must be empty and use default configurations before running the test.
9
10 For running this test, connection string of the Service Bus namespace and queue name
11 must be supplied.
12 */
13
Error Row 14, Column 1: "copyright header not properly configured - expected value: Copyright (c) Microsoft Corporation. All rights reserved. Licensed under the MIT License. " @azure/azure-sdk/github-source-headers
14 import {
15 ServiceBusClient,
16 SendableMessageInfo,
17 OnMessage,
18 OnError,
19 delay,
20 ReceiveMode
21 } from "../../src";
22
23 const connectionString = "";
24 const queueName = "";
25
26 const testDurationInMilliseconds = 60000 * 5 * 12 * 24 * 7; // 1 week
27
28 const messagesToProcess: Set<number> = new Set<number>();
29
30 let abandonAttempt = 0;
31 let abandonCount = 0;
32 let completeCount = 0;
33 let deadletterCount = 0;
34 let deferCount = 0;
35
36 let msgId = 1;
37
38 let snapshotIntervalID: any;
39
40 let isJobDone = false;
41
42 async function main(): Promise<void> {
43 snapshotIntervalID = setInterval(snapshot, 5000); // Every 5 seconds
44 const sendPromise = sendMessages();
45 const receivePromise = receiveMessages();
46 await Promise.all([sendPromise, receivePromise]);
47 }
48
49 async function sendMessages(): Promise<void> {
50 const ns = ServiceBusClient.createFromConnectionString(connectionString);
51 const client = ns.createQueueClient(queueName);
52 try {
53 const sender = client.createSender();
54
55 while (!isJobDone) {
56 const message: SendableMessageInfo = {
57 messageId: msgId,
58 body: "test",
59 label: `${msgId}`
60 };
61 messagesToProcess.add(msgId);
62 msgId++;
63 await sender.send(message);
64 await delay(2000); // Throttling send to not increase queue size
65 }
66 } finally {
67 await client.close();
68 await ns.close();
69 }
70 }
71
72 async function receiveMessages(): Promise<void> {
73 const ns = ServiceBusClient.createFromConnectionString(connectionString);
74 const client = ns.createQueueClient(queueName);
75
76 try {
77 const receiver = client.createReceiver(ReceiveMode.peekLock);
78 const onMessageHandler: OnMessage = async (brokeredMessage) => {
79 const receivedMsgId = brokeredMessage.messageId;
80
81 if (typeof receivedMsgId !== "number") {
82 throw new Error("MessageId is corrupt or is of unexpected type");
83 }
84
85 /*
86 Since there are 4 ways a message can be disposed namely abandon(), complete(),
87 defer() and deadletter(), the randomization factor is chosen to be 4.
88 */
89 const seed = Math.floor((Math.random() * 10) % 4);
90
91 switch (seed) {
92 case 0: {
93 abandonAttempt++;
94 if (brokeredMessage.deliveryCount === 10) {
95 abandonCount++;
96 if (messagesToProcess.has(receivedMsgId)) {
97 messagesToProcess.delete(receivedMsgId);
98 }
99 }
100 await brokeredMessage.abandon();
101 break;
102 }
103 case 1: {
104 completeCount++;
105 if (messagesToProcess.has(receivedMsgId)) {
106 messagesToProcess.delete(receivedMsgId);
107 }
108 await brokeredMessage.complete();
109 break;
110 }
111 case 2: {
112 deadletterCount++;
113 if (messagesToProcess.has(receivedMsgId)) {
114 messagesToProcess.delete(receivedMsgId);
115 }
116 await brokeredMessage.deadLetter();
117 break;
118 }
119 case 3: {
120 deferCount++;
121 if (messagesToProcess.has(receivedMsgId)) {
122 messagesToProcess.delete(receivedMsgId);
123 }
124 await brokeredMessage.defer();
125 break;
126 }
127 default: {
128 throw new Error("Unexpected seed");
129 }
130 }
131 };
132
133 const onErrorHandler: OnError = (err) => {
134 throw err;
135 };
136
137 receiver.registerMessageHandler(onMessageHandler, onErrorHandler, { autoComplete: false });
138 await delay(testDurationInMilliseconds);
139
140 isJobDone = true;
141
142 await receiver.close();
143 clearInterval(snapshotIntervalID);
144 } finally {
145 await client.close();
146 await ns.close();
147 }
148 }
149
150 function snapshot(): void {
151 console.log("Time : ", new Date());
152 console.log("Number of messages not processed yet : ", messagesToProcess.size);
153 console.log("Number of messages sent so far : ", msgId);
154 console.log("Number of messages abandoned : ", abandonCount);
155 console.log("Number of messages completed : ", completeCount);
156 console.log("Number of messages deadlettered : ", deadletterCount);
157 console.log("Number of messages deferred : ", deferCount);
158 console.log("Number of abandon attempts on messages : ", abandonAttempt);
159 console.log("\n");
160 }
161
162 main().catch((err) => {
163 console.log("Error occurred: ", err);
164 });

55 result = window.__env__[nameForBrowser];

68 break;
69 case EnvVarKeys.QUEUE_NAME_NO_PARTITION:

71 break;

83 break;

86 break;

88 defaultValue = "unpartitioned-topic-sessions";
89 break;
90 case EnvVarKeys.SUBSCRIPTION_NAME:

92 break;

14 import { ServiceBusClient, ReceiveMode, OnMessage, OnError, delay } from "@azure/service-bus";
15
16 // Define connection string and related Service Bus entity names here
17 const connectionString = "";
18 const queueName = "";

20 async function main(): Promise<void> {
21 await sendMessages();
22 await receiveMessage();

24
25 // Shuffle and send messages
26 async function sendMessages(): Promise<void> {
27 const sbClient = ServiceBusClient.createFromConnectionString(connectionString);
28 // If sending to a Topic, use `createTopicClient` instead of `createQueueClient`
29 const queueClient = sbClient.createQueueClient(queueName);
30 const sender = queueClient.createSender();
31
32 const data = [
33 { step: 1, title: "Shop" },
34 { step: 2, title: "Unpack" },
35 { step: 3, title: "Prepare" },
36 { step: 4, title: "Cook" },
37 { step: 5, title: "Eat" }
38 ];
39 const promises = new Array();
40 for (let index = 0; index < data.length; index++) {
41 const message = {
42 body: data[index],
43 label: "RecipeStep",
44 contentType: "application/json"
45 };
46 // the way we shuffle the message order is to introduce a tiny random delay before each of the messages is sent
47 promises.push(
48 delay(Math.random() * 30).then(async () => {
49 try {
50 await sender.send(message);
51 console.log("Sent message step:", data[index].step);
52 return;
53 } catch (err) {
54 console.log("Error while sending message", err);
55 return;
56 }
57 })
58 );
59 }
60 // wait until all the send tasks are complete
61 await Promise.all(promises);
62 await queueClient.close();
63 await sbClient.close();
64 }
65
66 async function receiveMessage(): Promise<void> {
67 const sbClient = ServiceBusClient.createFromConnectionString(connectionString);
68
69 // If receiving from a Subscription, use `createSubscriptionClient` instead of `createQueueClient`
70 const queueClient = sbClient.createQueueClient(queueName);
71
72 const deferredSteps = new Map();
73 let lastProcessedRecipeStep = 0;
74 try {
75 const onMessage: OnMessage = async (brokeredMessage) => {
76 if (
77 brokeredMessage.label === "RecipeStep" &&
78 brokeredMessage.contentType === "application/json"
79 ) {
80 const message = brokeredMessage.body;
81 // now let's check whether the step we received is the step we expect at this stage of the workflow
82 if (message.step === lastProcessedRecipeStep + 1) {
83 console.log("Process received message:", message);
84 lastProcessedRecipeStep++;
85 await brokeredMessage.complete();
86 } else {
87 // if this is not the step we expected, we defer the message, meaning that we leave it in the queue but take it out of
88 // the delivery order. We put it aside. To retrieve it later, we remeber its sequence number
89 const sequenceNumber = brokeredMessage.sequenceNumber;
90 deferredSteps.set(message.step, sequenceNumber);
91 console.log("Defer received message:", message);
92 await brokeredMessage.defer();
93 }
94 } else {
95 // we dead-letter the message if we don't know what to do with it.
96 console.log(
97 "Unknown message received, moving it to dead-letter queue ",
98 brokeredMessage.body
99 );
100 await brokeredMessage.deadLetter();
101 }
102 };
103 const onError: OnError = (err) => {
104 console.log(">>>>> Error occurred: ", err);
105 };
106
107 let receiver = queueClient.createReceiver(ReceiveMode.peekLock);
108 receiver.registerMessageHandler(onMessage, onError, { autoComplete: false }); // Disabling autoComplete so we can control when message can be completed, deferred or deadlettered
109 await delay(10000);
110 await receiver.close();
111 console.log("Total number of deferred messages:", deferredSteps.size);
112
113 receiver = queueClient.createReceiver(ReceiveMode.peekLock);
114 // Now we process the deferred messages
115 while (deferredSteps.size > 0) {
116 const step = lastProcessedRecipeStep + 1;
117 const sequenceNumber = deferredSteps.get(step);
118 const message = await receiver.receiveDeferredMessage(sequenceNumber);
119 if (message) {
120 console.log("Process deferred message:", message.body);
121 await message.complete();
122 } else {
123 console.log("No message found for step number ", step);
124 }
125 deferredSteps.delete(step);
126 lastProcessedRecipeStep++;
127 }
128 await queueClient.close();
129 } finally {
130 await sbClient.close();
131 }
132 }
133
134 main().catch((err) => {
135 console.log("Error occurred: ", err);
136 });

113 async function processMessageFromSession(sessionId: string): Promise<void> {
114 // If receiving from a Subscription, use `createSubscriptionClient` instead of `createQueueClient`

116

118 sessionId: sessionId
119 });
120
121 const messages = await sessionReceiver.receiveMessages(1, 10);
122
123 // Custom logic for processing the messages
124 if (messages.length > 0) {
125 // Update sessionState
126 if (messages[0].body.event_name === "Checkout") {
127 // Clear cart if customer exits, else retain items.
128 await sessionReceiver.setState(JSON.stringify([]));
129 } else if (messages[0].body.event_name === "Add Item") {
130 // Update cart if customer adds items and store it in session state.
131 const currentSessionState = await sessionReceiver.getState();
132 let newSessionState: string[] = [];
133 if (currentSessionState) {
134 newSessionState = JSON.parse(currentSessionState);
135 }
136 newSessionState.push(messages[0].body.event_details);
137 await sessionReceiver.setState(JSON.stringify(newSessionState));
138 }
139
140 console.log(
141 `Received message: Customer '${sessionReceiver.sessionId}': '${messages[0].body.event_name} ${
142 messages[0].body.event_details
143 }'`
144 );
145 await messages[0].complete();
146 } else {
147 console.log(`No events were received for Customer: ${sessionId}\n`);
148 }
149
150 await sessionReceiver.close();
151 await queueClient.close();
152 }

49 // Scheduling messages to be sent after 10 seconds from now
50 async function sendScheduledMessages(sbClient: ServiceBusClient): Promise<void> {
51 // If sending to a Topic, use `createTopicClient` instead of `createQueueClient`
52 const queueClient = sbClient.createQueueClient(queueName);
53 const sender = queueClient.createSender();
54
55 const messages: SendableMessageInfo[] = listOfScientists.map((scientist) => ({
56 body: `${scientist.firstName} ${scientist.lastName}`,
57 label: "Scientist"
58 }));
59
60 const timeNowUtc = new Date(Date.now());
61 const scheduledEnqueueTimeUtc = new Date(Date.now() + 10000);
62 console.log(`Time now in UTC: ${timeNowUtc}`);
63 console.log(
64 `Messages will appear in Service Bus after 10 seconds at: ${scheduledEnqueueTimeUtc}`
65 );
66
67 await sender.scheduleMessages(scheduledEnqueueTimeUtc, messages);
68 }
69
70 async function receiveMessages(sbClient: ServiceBusClient): Promise<void> {
71 // If receiving from a Subscription, use `createSubscriptionClient` instead of `createQueueClient`
72 const queueClient = sbClient.createQueueClient(queueName);
73
74 let numOfMessagesReceived = 0;
75 const onMessageHandler: OnMessage = async (brokeredMessage) => {
76 numOfMessagesReceived++;
77 console.log(`Received message: ${brokeredMessage.body} - ${brokeredMessage.label}`);
78 await brokeredMessage.complete();
79 };
80 const onErrorHandler: OnError = (err) => {
81 console.log("Error occurred: ", err);
82 };
83
84 console.log(`\nStarting receiver immediately at ${new Date(Date.now())}`);
85
86 let receiver = queueClient.createReceiver(ReceiveMode.peekLock);
87 receiver.registerMessageHandler(onMessageHandler, onErrorHandler);
88 await delay(5000);
89 await receiver.close();
90 console.log(`Received ${numOfMessagesReceived} messages.`);
91
92 await delay(5000);
93 receiver = queueClient.createReceiver(ReceiveMode.peekLock);
94
95 console.log(`\nStarting receiver at ${new Date(Date.now())}`);
96
97 receiver.registerMessageHandler(onMessageHandler, onErrorHandler);
98 await delay(5000);
99 await receiver.close();
100 console.log(`Received ${numOfMessagesReceived} messages.`);
101
102 await queueClient.close();
103 }
104
105 main().catch((err) => {
106 console.log("Error occurred: ", err);
107 });
